    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4fda4934_057236b6",
        "filename": "hw/android/goldfish/device.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 40,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-02-14T16:22:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If this is only used for the high-order bits of the name buffer address, I\u0027d recommend using something like \"name_addr_high\" for the name to make it more explicit.\n\nDo you know if this is something that should be saved in a snapshot file? If so we need the appropriate save/load callbacks for the bus state as well.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 40,
        "startChar": 11,
        "endLine": 40,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "d80391eba0f4c6a247957834e8bb6879801013c4",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6fa38db3_76b4a8fe",
        "filename": "hw/android/goldfish/device.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 50,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-02-14T16:22:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This probably should be part of the state (to properly support snapshotting at all times). And an accessor function like goldfish_guest_is64bit() defined here and declared goldfish/device.h would be preferable.\n\nGenerally speaking, global variables should be avoided, and they are a reason why rebooting is currently broken in the Android emulator. I\u0027d like to get rid of them as much as possible soon.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 50,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 50,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "d80391eba0f4c6a247957834e8bb6879801013c4",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6fa38db3_16127c41",
        "filename": "hw/android/goldfish/device.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 176,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2014-02-14T16:22:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Again, probably not guard this with TARGET_X86_64. Either rely on the fact that |ptr_high| will be 0 if \u0027GET_NAME_HIGH\u0027 is never called, or check against |goldfish_64bit_guest|.",
      "revId": "d80391eba0f4c6a247957834e8bb6879801013c4",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
